# VA To-Do Chrome Extension

## Project Overview
VA To-do is a simple note-taking Chrome extension for Virtual Assistants to organize their day-to-day schedule.

## Technical Stack
- Platform: Chrome extension
- Frontend: HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript (vanilla)

## Code Generation Rules

### 1. Project Structure
- Maintain the established modular folder structure
- Components in `/app/components`
- Services in `/app/services`
- Styles in `/app/styles`
- Assets in `/app/assets`
- Use semantic file and folder names

### 2. Code Style
- Use 2-space indentation consistently
- Keep line length below 100 characters
- Use kebab-case for file names
- Use camelCase for variables and functions
- Use PascalCase for class names

### 3. Component Guidelines
- Use semantic HTML tags
- Ensure components are responsive and accessible
- Follow the established component pattern (ES6 classes)
- Keep components focused on a single responsibility
- Use event delegation when appropriate

### 4. State Management
- Use the StorageService for persistent data
- Maintain a consistent state update pattern
- Use custom events for component communication

### 5. Security Guidelines
- Validate all user inputs
- Use Chrome storage API safely
- Follow extension security best practices
- Request minimal permissions

### 6. Performance Optimization
- Minimize DOM operations
- Use efficient selectors
- Optimize event listeners

### 7. Documentation
- Document all components, classes, and functions
- Maintain the README with any new features or changes
- Keep code comments relevant and helpful

## Best Practices

### 1. Code Quality
- Write reusable, readable, and clean code
- Avoid deeply nested logic
- Follow DRY principles
- Modularize code into helpers/utils

### 2. Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML tags
- Add appropriate ARIA attributes
- Ensure keyboard navigation
- Maintain good color contrast

### 3. Extension-specific
- Follow Chrome extension best practices
- Use background scripts only when necessary
- Handle browser events appropriately 